    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-05T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-05T03:00:00-05:00" n="437"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d437">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.002/11–548: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-05T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 5, 1948—4 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 5—8:36 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2106. Foreign Minister Wang Shih-chieh informs us Cabinet, under urgent plea from
                        Generalissimo,<note n="33" xml:id="d437fn33">Chiang Kai-shek, President of
                        the Republic of China.</note> has agreed remain in power few more days.
                    There are afoot in high Government circles plans for “radical” measures in
                    desperate effort improve situation. Cabinet is remaining in power pending final
                    decision this problem.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
